# Introduction

How are men and women of same households impacted by food insecurity?


# Research Design

In Iraq, we randomly sampled  households and randomly assigned them into two comparable groups (Group A vs. Group B). In the first phase, households in Group A took the phone survey (rCARI) while we conducted face-to-face (F2F* Households are classified according to the nature of their coping strategies) interviews (standard CARI) with households in Group B. Then in 2nd phase, we switch the survey mordality and compare the results on food security reporting.

# Data and Methods

## rCSI
The reduced Coping Strategies Index (rCSI) is an indicator used to compare the hardship faced by households due to shortage of food. The index measures the frequency and severity of the food consumption behaviours the households had to engage in due to food shortage in the 7 days prior to the survey.

## Minimum Dietary Diversity (MDD)
The Minimum Dietary Diversity (MDD) indicator is a food group diversity indicator that has been shown to reflect one key dimension of diet quality: micronutrient adequacy, summarised across 11 micronutrients. 

